---
description: Hexagonal architecture enforcement and dependency direction rules
applyTo: "backend/**/*.py"
---



Strict dependency direction — always inward, never outward.


```
backend/src/{{ project_slug }}/
├── core/                     # Domain layer (INNERMOST) — ZERO external deps
│   ├── base.py               # Entity, ValueObject, DomainEvent base classes
│   ├── errors.py             # DomainError hierarchy (NotFound, Conflict, Validation, Authorization)
│   ├── ports.py              # Port protocols: Repository[T], CachePort, EventBus, UnitOfWork
│   ├── entities/             # Domain entities (inherit Entity, dataclass(slots=True))
│   ├── value_objects/        # Immutable VOs (frozen=True, slots=True, inherit ValueObject)
│   ├── events/               # Domain events (frozen=True, slots=True, inherit DomainEvent)
│   └── enums/                # Domain enums (StrEnum + @unique + auto())
│
├── application/              # Use cases, orchestration, DTOs
│   ├── base_service.py       # BaseService (logging, event bus injection)
│   ├── base_dto.py           # BaseDTO (Pydantic BaseModel + ConfigDict)
│   ├── services/             # Inherit BaseService, depend on port protocols ONLY
│   ├── commands/             # Write-side inputs (frozen dataclasses)
│   ├── queries/              # Read-side inputs (frozen dataclasses)
│   ├── dtos/                 # Inherit BaseDTO, Annotated[..., Field(...)]
│   ├── mappers/              # Entity ↔ DTO mapping functions
│   └── tasks/                # Async task definitions (Celery signatures)
│
├── adapters/                 # Concrete port implementations
│   ├── persistence/          # DB: ORM models, repos, UoW, session, mixins
│   │   ├── base_repository.py
│   │   ├── mixins.py         # IdentityMixin, AuditMixin (ALL ORM models use these)
│   │   ├── models/           # SQLAlchemy 2.0+ (Mapped[] + mapped_column())
│   │   ├── repositories/     # Concrete repo implementations
│   │   ├── unit_of_work/     # SQLAlchemy UoW
│   │   └── session.py        # Async engine + session factory (single definition)
│   ├── cache/                # Redis + in-memory (implement CachePort)
│   ├── messaging/            # Event bus (implement EventBus)
│   ├── auth/                 # JWT / auth adapters
│   └── external/             # httpx clients, third-party API adapters
│
├── ports/                    # Presentation layer (OUTERMOST)
│   ├── api/                  # FastAPI REST
│   │   ├── app.py            # create_api_app() -> FastAPI
│   │   ├── dependencies.py   # ALL Depends() — DI wiring
│   │   ├── error_handlers.py # DomainError → HTTP status (ONLY place for HTTP codes)
│   │   ├── middleware/       # Rate limiting, request ID, CORS
│   │   └── routes/           # Thin routes — ZERO business logic
│   ├── web/                  # Jinja2 web UI
│   │   ├── app.py            # create_web_app() -> FastAPI
│   │   └── controllers/      # Call application services, never adapters
│   └── cli/                  # Click/Typer CLI
│       └── app.py            # create_cli_app() -> typer.Typer
│
├── config/                   # Settings, DI container, Celery
│   ├── settings.py           # AppSettings(BaseSettings) — single source, @lru_cache
│   ├── celery/               # Celery config (reads from AppSettings)
│   └── infra/                # DI container wiring (protocols → concrete adapters)
│
└── utils/                    # Framework-agnostic, pure functions, stdlib ONLY
    ├── enums.py              # Centralized enums (Environment, LogLevel, SortOrder, etc.)
    ├── validators.py         # Pure validation (keyword-only, raise ValueError)
    ├── logger_factory.py     # Structured logging setup
    └── ...                   # retry_policies, crypto_utils, file_utils, etc.
```


```
core/ ← application/ ← adapters/
                      ← ports/
                      ← config/
utils/ ← (all layers may import; utils imports from NO project layer)
```

| Layer            | May Import From                                              | NEVER Imports From                     |
| ---------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------ | -------------------------------------- |
| **core/**        | stdlib, utils/                                               | application/, adapters/, ports/, config/ |
| **application/** | core/ (protocols + base classes), utils/                     | adapters/, ports/, config/             |
| **adapters/**    | core/ (protocols), application/ (DTOs, mappers), utils/, libs | ports/                                 |
| **ports/**       | application/ (services, DTOs), config/, utils/               | core/ (directly), adapters/ (use DI)   |
| **config/**      | utils/, external libs                                        | core/, application/, adapters/, ports/ |
| **utils/**       | stdlib ONLY                                                  | ALL other project layers               |


| Concern                                  | ONLY In                 |
| ---------------------------------------- | ----------------------- |
| HTTP status codes, request/response      | `ports/api/`            |
| CLI exit codes, terminal output          | `ports/cli/`            |
| HTML rendering, form handling            | `ports/web/`            |
| Business rules, domain invariants        | `core/`                 |
| Use case orchestration, DTO mapping      | `application/`          |
| Database queries, ORM, SQL, sessions     | `adapters/persistence/` |
| Cache get/set/delete                     | `adapters/cache/`       |
| Event publish/subscribe                  | `adapters/messaging/`   |
| Environment variables, settings          | `config/settings.py`    |
| Pure, framework-agnostic helpers         | `utils/`                |


```python
from {{ project_slug }}.core.entities.user import User
from {{ project_slug }}.core.ports import CachePort
from {{ project_slug }}.application.services.user_service import UserService

from {{ project_slug }}.adapters.persistence import UserRepository  # core → adapter
from {{ project_slug }}.ports.api.routes import router              # core → port
```


ALL entry points use factory functions — no global mutable state:

- `create_api_app() -> FastAPI` in `ports/api/app.py`
- `create_web_app() -> FastAPI` in `ports/web/app.py`
- `create_cli_app() -> typer.Typer` in `ports/cli/app.py`
- `create_celery_app() -> Celery` in `config/celery.py`


- `config/infra/` wires port protocols to concrete adapters
- Constructor injection via typed parameters
- No service locator pattern, no global mutable state
- Routes NEVER instantiate dependencies — use `ports/api/dependencies.py`
